<h2 id="installation">Installation & Setup</h2>
<h3>Requirements</h3>
<ul>
    <li>PHP 7.4 or higher</li>
    <li>MySQL/MariaDB</li>
    <li>LEMP Stack (Linux, Nginx, MySQL, PHP)</li>
    <li>Google Maps API Key</li>
</ul>

<h3>Setup Instructions</h3>
<ol>
    <li>Clone the repository from <a href="https://github.com/kevsiraki/dont_Trip" target="_blank">GitHub</a>.</li>
    <li>
        Configure the environment variables in the <code>.env</code> file:
        <pre><code>
DB_HOST=your_database_host
DB_NAME=your_database_name
DB_USER=your_database_user
DB_PASSWORD=your_database_password
GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=your_google_maps_api_key
        </code></pre>
    </li>
    <li>Import the SQL schema from the <code>db</code> folder to set up your database.</li>
    <li>Run the server with Nginx and ensure that PHP-FPM is configured correctly.</li>
    <li>Access the app at <code>http://localhost</code> or your server's IP address.</li>
</ol>

<hr />

<h2 id="usage">Usage</h2>
<p>Once the app is installed, users can create an account, plan trips, search for locations, and add stops to their route. The dark/light mode adjusts automatically based on user settings or local time, and the app offers extensive details for each place along the route. Users can save search history and popular places, as well as configure personal preferences for optimal trip planning.</p>

<hr />

<h2 id="troubleshooting">Troubleshooting</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>SSL Issues:</strong> Ensure that the SSL certificates are properly configured in your Nginx server block.</li>
    <li><strong>Database Connectivity:</strong> Double-check the database credentials in the <code>.env</code> file.</li>
    <li><strong>API Key Errors:</strong> Verify that the Google Maps API key is correctly set in <code>.env</code> and has appropriate permissions.</li>
</ul>

